In December 1977, at the age of 38, Howard was appointed Treasurer. During his five years in the position, he became an adherent of free-market economics,Kelly (1994), p. 102. which was challenging economic orthodoxies in place for most of the century.Kelly (1994), pp. 50â€“53. He came to favour tax reform including broad-based taxation (later the GST), a freer industrial system including the dismantling of the centralised wage-fixing system, the abolition of compulsory trade unionism, privatisation and deregulation.